  "body": "Hi,\n\ni the following setup geth seems to stop importing blocks after a while:\n\nWe have a java application which works as a proxy. It gets the rpc getWork request from the ethminer forwards it to the geth node and adjusts the response. If the header hash has changed, the java application sends out a rpc call getBlockByNumber with parameter \"pending\" in order to get the pending block information. If the ethminer finds a solution it does the rpc call submitWork. Then this solution with reduced difficulty is send by the proxy to the node as well.\n\nSince most solutions with reduced difficulty are not valid for the livenet it says correctly:\n\"Invalid header on mined block: Header's nonce is invalid (= 5228bad4da2aff10)\"\n\nAfter a while (on my ubuntu system after a couple of days; on users' windows machines after a day) it stops importing blocks/ sending out new work.\n\nSo to sum it up, following rpc calls are done:\n*getWork\n*submitWork\n*getBlockByNumber(\"pending\",...)\n\nSomehow there is might be a racey mutex or something.\n\nWould be nice if you could check it out.\n\nmaybe related to: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/1930\nor https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/1849\n\nI 'll report if that happens on 1.23 too.\n",
